t: A Psalm and Song at the dedication of the house of David.
I*p will extol thee, O Lord;*s for thou hast lifted me up, and hast not made my foes to rejoice over me.
O*p Lord*s my God, I cried unto thee, and thou hast healed me.
O*p Lord,*s thou hast brought up my soul from the grave: thou hast kept me alive, that I should not go down to the pit.
Sing*p unto the Lord,*s O ye saints of his, and give thanks at the remembrance of his holiness.
For*p his anger endureth but a moment; in his favour is life: weeping may endure for a night, but joy cometh in the morning.
And*p in my prosperity I said, I shall never be moved.
Lord,*sp by thy favour thou hast made my mountain to stand strong: thou didst hide thy face, and I was troubled.
I*p cried to thee, O Lord;*s and unto the Lord*s I made supplication.
What*p profit is there in my blood, when I go down to the pit? Shall the dust praise thee? shall it declare thy truth?
Hear,*p O Lord,*s and have mercy upon me: Lord,*s be thou my helper.
Thou*p hast turned for me my mourning into dancing: thou hast put off my sackcloth, and girded me with gladness;
To*p the end that my glory may sing praise to thee, and not be silent. O Lord*s my God, I will give thanks unto thee for ever.
